Definitely not enough sins on the helicopter scene. First off, it would easily lift the tow truck on its own. Secondly, lifting the car(s) without making them lose contact to the ground will reduce their traction, that is low because they're off-road anyway, to the point where it should easily overpower several cars in terms of lateral movement.
Thirdly, the cliff scene, in particular that 5 cars in a line can't pull the helicopter around a turn, but one car with NOS can, while still off road with little grip.
Also, the helicopter is, at that point, clearly carrying the weight of several cars entirely, which I'm not sure is possible, but if it iss, it should have been able to just ignore the tow truck at the beginning.

And so on and so forth, you get the idea.

I'm wondering about the perfect CinemaSins movie:
Filmed in real time, so there is no "what happens before this scene?"
All research is done in real time, even though it might take 2 hours, you have to show EVERYTHING about it
Relatives have to be ACTUAL relatives
No additional characters or cameos, just the important characters
BUT, loads of extra characters so it doesn't concentrate on just a couple of central characters
Locations have to be specific AND non-specific, as people aren't stupid and won't know places
Whenever anyone tries to do something, they have to fail multiple times, and each one is shown
Anytime anyone has to learn to do something, you have to show ALL of their training


In other words, the film will be following someone's actual life, showing everywhere they go, and all of the mundane things they do - this would be THE MOST BORING FILM EVER MADE but CinemaSins wouldn't be able to use their "normal" sins, instead they'd complain that nothing is happening, things are too realistic, and they're showing too much detail 😛
